full_text:
Our conversation on bipartisan problem solving continues w/ a discussion on COVID-19.

Folks are working & taking classes from home.

That's why it's critical we expand access to broadband. And @WhipClyburn & I have a bipartisan bill to do just that: https://t.co/rYNoVtlMNi #MI06 https://t.co/VhzQ8lTCra

full_text: Finished up a great day w/ @SecretaryCarson touring the @KzooGospel. Pastor Brown & his team are devoted servants to our community & we cannot thank them enough for all they do for KZoo families. When we all work together, there is nothing we can't do. #MI06 https://t.co/tsKXweEeAF

retweeted_text: Thanks @RepFredUpton for speaking with us between voting in congress in Washington D.C. today. We talk about a Pfizer vaccine and impacts for West Michigan, a second stimulus package and unemployment, and students returning to school this fall. Watch tonight on @wwmtnews . https://t.co/X2WViru4fD

full_text: Throughout the COVID crisis, we've been working hard to support folks in SW MI & provide them w/ helpful info. We know state & local budgets have been decimated by the COVID outbreak, & so many critical services rely on this funding. That's why I've intro’d the bipartisan SMART Fund to provide $500B to every state, county, & community to weather this crisis. #MI06

retweeted_text: Join our teletown hall with @RepFredUpton, live now! Call 833-380-0616 to participate.

full_text:
Today @ 11 AM, I’ll be joining Michigan State AARP Director Paula Cunningham on a Teletown hall to discuss the COVID-19 pandemic and its disproportionate impact on older folks in Michigan. 

Be sure to tune in by dialing 833-380-0616 on your phone. #MI06

full_text: It's no secret that Independence Day is going to look a little different this year. Parades, picnics, & fireworks may be cancelled, but the American spirit lives on. Wherever you're spending the 4th of July weekend, have fun, be safe, & wear your mask! Happy Independence Day! 🇺🇸

This is a time of trial for our state and our country.

I’ll join fellow MI members @RepFredUpton, @RepMoolenaar and @RepHuizenga tomorrow from 7-8PM as @WLNS and @WOODTV hold a TV town hall to discuss how we can face the challenges before us. Tune in: https://t.co/kIHC3sCPyg

full_text:
I spoke this morning to a number of community leaders and law enforcement, and we will continue to maintain regular contact as we move forward.
 
All our hearts remain with George Floyd’s family as we continue to grieve.

This week, legislation led by Problem Solvers @RepDeanPhillips & 
@RepFredUpton passed the House of Representatives.  This bipartisan legislation helps ensure our small businesses & entrepreneurs are protected & have the support they need to get through these challenging times. https://t.co/9U0oiZ9OWz

full_text: .@WWMTnews covered @WhipClyburn's and my "Rural Broadband Acceleration Act," our bipartisan effort to increase high-speed internet in rural America. If we can pass this bipartisan bill and implement it, it might be one of the biggest leaps for rural America in our lifetime. #MI06 https://t.co/QXrCCRNo1e

full_text: In the US, nearly 1 in 4 rural households can't connect to the internet, & it's often too slow & too expensive for those who do have access. Along w/ @WhipClyburn, I'm leading bipartisan legislation to expand rural broadband service & keep folks connected. https://t.co/nIquFvzuxn

retweeted_text: My new bill with @RepFredUpton would allow broadband expansion efforts like this one to access FCC funds immediately, allowing Americans to get access to high-speed internet in their homes sooner. https://t.co/ZJx87Vk2AQ

full_text: 53% of rural students lack access to high-speed, home Internet compared to only 23% of their suburban peers. This disparity negatively impacts educational opportunities for rural students & I'm leading the Rural Broadband Acceleration Act to close this gap.https://t.co/nIquFvzuxn

WED| @RepFredUpton (R-Michigan) discusses the federal response to the coronavirus pandemic

Live at 8am! https://t.co/AGi9AnAhjL

full_text: Full day w/ @ProbSolveCaucus. We discussed the possibility of a House vote on the Paycheck Protection Flexibility Act as early as next week. This legislation will make commonsense reforms to improve the #PPP to better help small biz & protect small biz jobs. More tomorrow! #MI06

Just heard from HHS - Michigan has received its allocation of remdesivir today. The state got a shipment of 128 cases of the drug, which works out to 5,120 doses. 

Remdesivir has shown promising results for those severely infected by COVID-19. #MI06

I've talked nearly daily w/ the Governor & local leaders. It's clear from my discussions our states & small communities need help. That's why yesterday I helped introduce the bipartisan #SMARTFund to get resources into the right hands.

A heartfelt thank you for all that you do to keep us safe & healthy during this time. #InItTogether #MI06 https://t.co/2zALB7cP7s

full_text: In times of crisis, Americans have always come together to help their neighbors & lend a hand. This is clear across #MI06 & around the country as folks are showing what it means to be a hero & give hope to our great nation. We're tough, we're Americans, & we're #InItTogether. 🇺🇸 https://t.co/p5zavkA5R2

full_text: It’s no secret that our nation is enduring tough times, but with each sunset that comes and goes here in #MI06, we’re one day closer to winning this fight & I know that the American spirit will ultimately prevail. We’re strong, we’re resilient, & we’re #InItTogether. https://t.co/48U8Z14kV0

The #PaycheckProtectionProgram has helped millions of small businesses and workers — and this lifeline resumes today.

These loans are 𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗶𝘃𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲 when used for payroll, rent, or to rehire laid-off workers.

Visit 🌐https://t.co/OCaElOIPap for more info. https://t.co/DUozfXIP5i

full_text:
Small businesses can apply for the Paycheck Protection Program again today at 10:30 ET. 

The #PPP is a solemn promise from Congress to our nation's small biz, helping to protect jobs & keep small biz afloat.

retweeted_text: The Paycheck Protection Program is supporting over 1.6 million small businesses in all 50 states. Congress should provide more funding NOW to keep #PPP going! https://t.co/xnelCWj8Iv

full_text: This critical shipment of med supplies contained tens of thousands of medical masks, gloves, thermometers, and hospital gowns. These supplies will greatly help protect both patients & health care providers & help fight the spread of COVID-19 in SW MI. #InItTogether #MI06 https://t.co/OD17RfCCkO

full_text: Yesterday was another busy day of conference calls at my kitchen table. I spoke w/ @stevenmnuchin1 about replenishing PPP loans and discussed how to safely reopen our economy with the bipartisan Problem Solvers Caucus. It’s safe to say that I’m very glad I kept my landline! #MI06

The #PaycheckProtectionProgram is a lifeline for small businesses on Main Street across America.
 
Congress must urgently pass additional funding for this bipartisan, job-saving program.
 
There’s no time to waste. Small businesses need our help – and they need it NOW.

full_text: Heard that coronavirus tests headed to Bronson Hospital in Kzoo were being held up, so our office made a few phone calls to track them down. Just now, 1,000 Cepheid tests were delivered! So important as our community continues responding to this health crisis #MI06 #InItTogether

The @USTreasury and @SBAgov’s #PaycheckProtectionProgram provides much-needed certainty and #SmallBizRelief.
 
If small businesses use the money for payroll, mortgage interest, rent, and utilities, that portion of the loan will be forgiven.

Reduce spread of #COVID19. When in public, use a cloth face covering that 
✔️Reaches above nose & below chin, completely covering mouth & nostrils
✔️Fits snugly against sides of your face
✔️Is made of multiple layers of cloth that you can breathe through

Take action to slow the spread of #COVID19 by wearing a cloth face covering in public spaces, keeping at least 6 feet of physical distance, & frequently washing your hands.
Make a cloth face covering from a t-shirt, scarf or cloth napkin. Learn more at https://t.co/bihJ3xEM15. https://t.co/IVZklVYUtS

retweeted_text: #COVID19 UPDATE: Small businesses can now apply for the #PaycheckProtectionProgram. The program is designed to keep small business workers employed & provide small businesses with capital through the nation’s banks & other lending institutions. Apply here: https://t.co/JvWDCXtDP4

full_text:
Today small businesses can apply for the #PaycheckProtectionProgram, which will help folks keep their businesses afloat and their employees on payroll.

Learn more by visiting https://t.co/wvNY05Zxfs. #MI06 #InItTogether https://t.co/SNVQafIDcF

Earlier this week, we lost a wonderful friend and hero who we will never forget - Bud Baker.

This vicious virus did what even the ravages of war could not. Bud was one of our most decorated veterans and celebrated citizens in Berrien County, and he will be dearly missed. #MI06 https://t.co/hZw3twCCJH

full_text:
In my Kitchen Table update yesterday, I mentioned how folks need to be aware of scams during the coronavirus crisis. I received a call like that earlier this week. 

If you get that call, hang up on those folks ASAP. #MI06 #InItTogether https://t.co/2wjt3ZON4p

A number of calls today with my MI colleagues, the Problem Solvers Caucus, and small businesses. 

Tomorrow I will join our two U.S. Senators on a FEMA conference call to see if we can get more PPE for MI’s health care workers.

Let’s keep working! #MI06 #InItTogether https://t.co/cucDZ6PAec

Read today's Kitchen Table update here: https://t.co/IeuRF0mT1J #MI06 #InItTogether https://t.co/V3ztxLzQxx

The coronavirus crisis is a lonely time for friends and family as we are not able to reach out like we always have. We all want the nightmare to end...here, and around the world.

I want to share a prayer by Thomas Merton that has always been close to our family’s heart...

full_text:
The Region IV Area Agency on Aging has set up an info-line to help seniors during the coronavirus crisis. 

The 24-hour info-line is 800-654-2810. 

It’s staffed w/ experts able to provide answers and resources specific to local seniors’ needs. https://t.co/K5Hp9MLwGU #MI06

full_text:
I‘ve been working for the most of the week at my kitchen table, talking w/ as many folks as possible - farmers, church & school leaders, & public health officials. We want to know what folks have, what they need, & what challenges they‘re facing. 

We’re in this together! #MI06 https://t.co/KuWnlSG7E6

Folks are facing real challenges during the coronavirus crisis, and we all need to do our part to help each other out.

If you need assistance, there are a number of resources available. As always, you can contact my office and we can try to help: https://t.co/V34ltAuVvX https://t.co/18wLykyJyy

Practice social distancing by putting space between yourself and others. Continue to practice healthy habits, like washing your hands for at least 20 seconds and staying home if you’re sick, to help slow the spread of #COVID19. 
Learn more: https://t.co/RhqzGyUzcH. https://t.co/kFgOsiRXrf

retweeted_text: WIC services at Kalamazoo County HCS continue although the number of in-person visits is being limited. If you have any questions or concerns about continued WIC services, please call us at 269-373-5002. WIC is working to do appointments by phone to ensure WIC services continue.

▪️ Expands testing for all Americans
 
▪️ Provides paid sick leave for workers
 
▪️ Gives small businesses the flexibility they need to care for their employees and remain open

#MI06 https://t.co/0IWBa1OeqP
